post_text:
Reminder:

There is a designated phone number for sickness that could be Covid related. The phone can be contacted 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. The phone number is 812-577-7140. Make sure to contact or text the phone if your child or someone in the home has Covid symptoms, has been tested for Covid, or if you are unsure if your child's symptoms are Covid related.
Starting 8/25, the state of Indiana is now requiring all students who live in a home with someone who has been Covid tested to be excluded from school until tests results are received. Test results must be submitted to the school from the location of the test. All absences related to Covid are excused. #rise_up

post_text: Congratulations to Ryan Works, 7th grader at OCEMS, for making the region 2 blue team for the All American Softball Games in August hosted at the USA softball Hall of Fame stadium in Oklahoma City. Designation to a USA Softball All-American team is the highest honor a player can receive and instantly brands the player as one of the top athletes in the United States. post_text: High school students should be receiving their 2020-2021 schedules in the mail today or tomorrow. They can also be viewed online through Powerschool. If a student would like to request a schedule change, please email Ms. Sauerhage at csauerhage@risingsun.k12.in.us. Not all changes will be available due to class availability or conflicts with required courses. If you wish to come into the school in person, a student needs to call the high school at 438-2652 to make an appointment. No schedule changes will be permitted after Monday, July 27th. Please email Ms. Sauerhage if you have any questions.

post_text: The Ohio County Community Foundation would like to announce that the 2020 Future Generations Scholarship application is currently available online at occfrisingsun.com . The due date is July 31st at 3:00 p.m. Current year RSHS Seniors will need: final high school transcript, college acceptance letter and all community service hours completed before they can complete the application. Returning college applicants will need their Spring transcript to complete the application. You must reapply each year and can receive the scholarship up to 5 times maximum. If you have any questions, need application help or want to check on Community Service Hours, please contact Christy Elbright at celbright@occfrisingsun or 812-438-9401.

Common Question

Do kids have to complete assignments by Wednesday each week?

Answer: Kids will have the whole week to complete the work so assignments can be turned in Sunday night of that week. Teachers will be accessible Monday-Wednesday from 9:00-3:00 for help. Many teachers will check emails after these hours and on different days, but these are their mandated days and hours to assist students quickly.

Many teachers will check emails after these hours and on different days, but these are their mandated days and hours to assist students quickly.

Due to the Governor’s announcement on Monday, all offices including the Superintendent’s office will be closed. Someone will come to the office once a day to check voicemail and return calls. Additionally, the food delivery will occur on One day. All five days worth of breakfasts and lunches will be delivered on Mondays.

3. Sign up for food delivery, email Branden Roeder (above) or call 812-438-2655 to leave a voicemail. Please leave name, phone number, and address.

PreK Registration

Tonight’s registration will be handled differently. Staff members will be at the front doors of the office with registration packets to hand out to parents. Parents will be asked a quick questionnaire involving student name, parent name, contact number, residential address, and does the child have a sibling in our district? Guardians will have until April 1 to turn in the packets. Birth certificate and shot records will not be required until a later date. Also, a meet the teacher date will occur later in the year. Our staff plan to keep track of the order of first come, first serve as guardians pick up packets. The procedures have changed in hopes to limit the amount of visitors in our buildings during the COVID-19 spread. If you have questions, please contact the OCEMS at 812-438-2626.

shared_text:
University of Evansville Physician Assistant Program is with Ashley Vecchiola at University of Evansville Physician Assistant Program.
March 4 at 10:05 AM · Evansville, IN ·

With the CASPA opening rapidly approaching, we want to introduce you to some more faces of UEPA! First up, Ashley Vecchiola! A Rising Sun, IN native,
Ashley got her Bachelor’s in Biology at Northern Kentucky University.

What made you want to be a PA?
I loved the flexibility of the career, since I am interested in multiple specialties. I also really liked that the career allows for more interactions with patients.

Why UEPA? Or what makes UEPA different than other PA Programs?
UEPA felt like the right choice for me since the very start. I love that this program is striving to create not only competent providers, but also compassionate and empathetic providers, as I feel like these are very important traits that providers often lack. Also, our professors and faculty are very invested in us, our well-being, and our success.

We are so grateful to have Ashley in the UEPA Family! 💜 #pastudent #physicianassistantstudent #futurepa #futurephysicianassistant #paschool #family #physicianassistant @ University of Evansville Physician Assistant Program
